#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an7.64"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.64:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.64:0.2"
msgid "6. Abyākatavagga "
msgstr "6. The Undeclared Points "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an7.64:0.3"
msgid "64. Kodhanasutta "
msgstr "64. Irritable "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an7.64:1.1"
msgid "“Sattime, bhikkhave, dhammā sapattakantā sapattakaraṇā kodhanaṃ āgacchanti itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these seven things that please and assist an enemy happen to an irritable woman or man. "

msgctxt "an7.64:1.2"
msgid "Katame satta? "
msgstr "What seven? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.64:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa evaṃ icchati: "
msgstr "Firstly, an enemy wishes for an enemy: "

msgctxt "an7.64:1.4"
msgid "‘aho vatāyaṃ dubbaṇṇo assā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only they’d become ugly!’ "

msgctxt "an7.64:1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.64:1.6"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa vaṇṇavatāya nandati. "
msgstr "Because an enemy doesn’t like to have a beautiful enemy. "

# NOTE: I think kappitaka refers to the complex hairdos of the time, not a mere trim: http://www.kalacakra.org/mandala/sanchi2.jpg
#. VAR: Kodhanoyaṃ → kodhanāyaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: odātavatthavasano → odātavatthavāsano (s1-3) | odātavasano (mr)
msgctxt "an7.64:1.7"
msgid "Kodhanoyaṃ, bhikkhave, purisapuggalo kodhābhibhūto kodhapareto, kiñcāpi so hoti sunhāto suvilitto kappitakesamassu odātavatthavasano; "
msgstr "An irritable person, overcome and overwhelmed by anger, is ugly, even though they’re nicely bathed and anointed, with hair and beard dressed, and wearing white clothes. "

msgctxt "an7.64:1.8"
msgid "atha kho so dubbaṇṇova hoti kodhābhibhūto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.64:1.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo sapattakanto sapattakaraṇo kodhanaṃ āgacchati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā. (1) "
msgstr "This is the first thing that pleases and assists an enemy which happens to an irritable woman or man. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an7.64:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa evaṃ icchati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, an enemy wishes for an enemy: "

msgctxt "an7.64:2.2"
msgid "‘aho vatāyaṃ dukkhaṃ sayeyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only they’d sleep badly!’ "

msgctxt "an7.64:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.64:2.4"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa sukhaseyyāya nandati. "
msgstr "Because an enemy doesn’t like to have an enemy who sleeps well. "

msgctxt "an7.64:2.5"
msgid "Kodhanoyaṃ, bhikkhave, purisapuggalo kodhābhibhūto kodhapareto, kiñcāpi so pallaṅke seti gonakatthate paṭalikatthate kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇe sauttaracchade ubhatolohitakūpadhāne; "
msgstr "An irritable person, overcome and overwhelmed by anger, sleeps badly, even though they sleep on a couch spread with woolen covers—shag-piled, pure white, or embroidered with flowers—and spread with a fine deer hide, with a canopy above and red pillows at both ends. "

msgctxt "an7.64:2.6"
msgid "atha kho so dukkhaññeva seti kodhābhibhūto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.64:2.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo sapattakanto sapattakaraṇo kodhanaṃ āgacchati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā. (2) "
msgstr "This is the second thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.95, sc3
msgctxt "an7.64:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa evaṃ icchati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, an enemy wishes for an enemy: "

msgctxt "an7.64:3.2"
msgid "‘aho vatāyaṃ na pacurattho assā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only they don’t get all they need!’ "

msgctxt "an7.64:3.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.64:3.4"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa pacuratthatāya nandati. "
msgstr "Because an enemy doesn’t like to have an enemy who gets all they need. "

msgctxt "an7.64:3.5"
msgid "Kodhanoyaṃ, bhikkhave, purisapuggalo kodhābhibhūto kodhapareto, anatthampi gahetvā ‘attho me gahito’ti maññati, atthampi gahetvā ‘anattho me gahito’ti maññati. "
msgstr "When an irritable person, overcome and overwhelmed by anger, gets what they don’t need they think ‘I’ve got what I need!’ When they get what they need they think ‘I’ve got what I don’t need.’ "

msgctxt "an7.64:3.6"
msgid "Tassime dhammā aññamaññaṃ vipaccanīkā gahitā dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti kodhābhibhūtassa. "
msgstr "When an angry person gets these things that are the exact opposite of what they need, it’s for their lasting harm and suffering. "

msgctxt "an7.64:3.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo sapattakanto sapattakaraṇo kodhanaṃ āgacchati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā. (3) "
msgstr "This is the third thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an7.64:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa evaṃ icchati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, an enemy wishes for an enemy: "

msgctxt "an7.64:4.2"
msgid "‘aho vatāyaṃ na bhogavā assā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only they weren’t wealthy!’ "

msgctxt "an7.64:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.64:4.4"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa bhogavatāya nandati. "
msgstr "Because an enemy doesn’t like to have an enemy who is wealthy. "

msgctxt "an7.64:4.5"
msgid "Kodhanassa, bhikkhave, purisapuggalassa kodhābhibhūtassa kodhaparetassa, yepissa te honti bhogā uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatā bāhābalaparicitā sedāvakkhittā dhammikā dhammaladdhā, tepi rājāno rājakosaṃ pavesenti kodhābhibhūtassa. "
msgstr "When a person is irritable, overcome and overwhelmed by anger, the rulers seize the legitimate wealth they’ve earned by their efforts, built up with their own hands, gathered by the sweat of their brow. "

msgctxt "an7.64:4.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo sapattakanto sapattakaraṇo kodhanaṃ āgacchati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā. (4) "
msgstr "This is the fourth thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an7.64:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa evaṃ icchati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, an enemy wishes for an enemy: "

msgctxt "an7.64:5.2"
msgid "‘aho vatāyaṃ na yasavā assā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only they weren’t famous!’ "

msgctxt "an7.64:5.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.64:5.4"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa yasavatāya nandati. "
msgstr "Because an enemy doesn’t like to have a famous enemy. "

msgctxt "an7.64:5.5"
msgid "Kodhanoyaṃ, bhikkhave, purisapuggalo kodhābhibhūto kodhapareto, yopissa so hoti yaso appamādādhigato, tamhāpi dhaṃsati kodhābhibhūto. "
msgstr "When a person is irritable, overcome and overwhelmed by anger, any fame they have acquired by diligence falls to dust. "

msgctxt "an7.64:5.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo sapattakanto sapattakaraṇo kodhanaṃ āgacchati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā. (5) "
msgstr "This is the fifth thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an7.64:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa evaṃ icchati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, an enemy wishes for an enemy: "

msgctxt "an7.64:6.2"
msgid "‘aho vatāyaṃ na mittavā assā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only they had no friends!’ "

msgctxt "an7.64:6.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.64:6.4"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa mittavatāya nandati. "
msgstr "Because an enemy doesn’t like to have an enemy with friends. "

msgctxt "an7.64:6.5"
msgid "Kodhanaṃ, bhikkhave, purisapuggalaṃ kodhābhibhūtaṃ kodhaparetaṃ, yepissa te honti mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā, tepi ārakā parivajjanti kodhābhibhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "When a person is irritable, overcome and overwhelmed by anger, their friends and colleagues, relatives and kin avoid them from afar. "

msgctxt "an7.64:6.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, chaṭṭho dhammo sapattakanto sapattakaraṇo kodhanaṃ āgacchati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā. (6) "
msgstr "This is the sixth thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.96, sc7
msgctxt "an7.64:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa evaṃ icchati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, an enemy wishes for an enemy: "

msgctxt "an7.64:7.2"
msgid "‘aho vatāyaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only, when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell!’ "

msgctxt "an7.64:7.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.64:7.4"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, sapatto sapattassa sugatigamane nandati. "
msgstr "Because an enemy doesn’t like to have an enemy who goes to a good place. "

msgctxt "an7.64:7.5"
msgid "Kodhanoyaṃ, bhikkhave, purisapuggalo kodhābhibhūto kodhapareto kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr "When a person is irritable, overcome and overwhelmed by anger, they do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an7.64:7.6"
msgid "So kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā vācāya … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.64:7.7"
msgid "kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati kodhābhibhūto. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "an7.64:7.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, sattamo dhammo sapattakanto sapattakaraṇo kodhanaṃ āgacchati itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā. (7) "
msgstr "This is the seventh thing that pleases and assists an enemy which happens to an irritable woman or man. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an7.64:8.1"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, satta dhammā sapattakantā sapattakaraṇā kodhanaṃ āgacchanti itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vāti. "
msgstr "These are the seven things that please and assist an enemy which happen to an irritable woman or man. "

# NOTE: For these difficult verses, in addition to BB, I have consulted Nyanamoli’s more poetic rendering (http://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/an/an07/an07.060.nymo.html) as well as Thanissaro (http://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/an/an07/an07.060.than.html).
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an7.64:9.1"
msgid "Kodhano dubbaṇṇo hoti, "
msgstr "An irritable person is ugly "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:9.2"
msgid "atho dukkhampi seti so; "
msgstr "and they sleep badly. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:9.3"
msgid "Atho atthaṃ gahetvāna, "
msgstr "When they get what they need, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: adhipajjati → adhigacchati (si) | paṭipajjati (s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.64:9.4"
msgid "anatthaṃ adhipajjati. "
msgstr "they take it to be what they don’t need. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an7.64:10.1"
msgid "Tato kāyena vācāya, "
msgstr "An angry person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:10.2"
msgid "vadhaṃ katvāna kodhano; "
msgstr "kills with body or speech; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:10.3"
msgid "Kodhābhibhūto puriso, "
msgstr "overcome with anger, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:10.4"
msgid "dhanajāniṃ nigacchati. "
msgstr "they lose their wealth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an7.64:11.1"
msgid "Kodhasammadasammatto, "
msgstr "Mad with anger, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: āyasakyaṃ → āyasakkhaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.64:11.2"
msgid "āyasakyaṃ nigacchati; "
msgstr "they fall into disgrace. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:11.3"
msgid "Ñātimittā suhajjā ca, "
msgstr "Relatives, friends, and loved ones "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:11.4"
msgid "parivajjanti kodhanaṃ. "
msgstr "avoid an irritable person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an7.64:12.1"
msgid "Anatthajanano kodho, "
msgstr "Anger creates harm; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:12.2"
msgid "kodho cittappakopano; "
msgstr "anger upsets the mind. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:12.3"
msgid "Bhayamantarato jātaṃ, "
msgstr "That person doesn’t recognize "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:12.4"
msgid "taṃ jano nāvabujjhati. "
msgstr "the danger that arises within. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an7.64:13.1"
msgid "Kuddho atthaṃ na jānāti, "
msgstr "An angry person doesn’t know the good. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:13.2"
msgid "kuddho dhammaṃ na passati; "
msgstr "An angry person doesn’t see the truth. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:13.3"
msgid "Andhatamaṃ tadā hoti, "
msgstr "When a person is beset by anger, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:13.4"
msgid "yaṃ kodho sahate naraṃ. "
msgstr "only blind darkness is left. "

# NOTE: I am not at all confident of these lines. I think this is what it means, but i admit I can’t completely justify it. BB has “When an angry person causes damage/whether easily or with difficulty”, Nyanamoli has “Someone a man in anger hurts;/But, when his anger is later spent/With difficulty or with ease,”. But can we take viya to mean vā? Thanissaro has “He takes pleasure in bad deeds as if they were good,” evidently following Hare in reading uparoceti “A man in wrath finds pleasure in bad deeds/as in good deeds.”
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.97, sc14
msgctxt "an7.64:14.1"
msgid "Yaṃ kuddho uparodheti, "
msgstr "An angry person destroys with ease "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:14.2"
msgid "sukaraṃ viya dukkaraṃ; "
msgstr "what was hard to build. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:14.3"
msgid "Pacchā so vigate kodhe, "
msgstr "Afterwards, when the anger is spent, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:14.4"
msgid "aggidaḍḍhova tappati. "
msgstr "they’re tormented as if burnt by fire. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
#. VAR: padasseti → sadasseti (bj) | paṭhamaṃ dasseti (s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.64:15.1"
msgid "Dummaṅkuyaṃ padasseti, "
msgstr "Their look betrays their sulkiness "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:15.2"
msgid "dhūmaṃ dhūmīva pāvako; "
msgstr "like a fire’s smoky plume. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:15.3"
msgid "Yato patāyati kodho, "
msgstr "And when their anger flares up, "

# NOTE: See BB’s note for the difficulties with this verse.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:15.4"
msgid "yena kujjhanti mānavā. "
msgstr "they make others angry. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
#. VAR: Nāssa hirī na ottappaṃ → na assa hirī ottappañca (mr)
msgctxt "an7.64:16.1"
msgid "Nāssa hirī na ottappaṃ, "
msgstr "They have no conscience or prudence, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:16.2"
msgid "na vāco hoti gāravo; "
msgstr "nor any respectful speech. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:16.3"
msgid "Kodhena abhibhūtassa, "
msgstr "One overcome by anger "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:16.4"
msgid "na dīpaṃ hoti kiñcanaṃ. "
msgstr "has no island refuge anywhere. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an7.64:17.1"
msgid "Tapanīyāni kammāni, "
msgstr "The deeds that torment a man "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:17.2"
msgid "yāni dhammehi ārakā; "
msgstr "are far from those that are good. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:17.3"
msgid "Tāni ārocayissāmi, "
msgstr "I’ll explain them now; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:17.4"
msgid "taṃ suṇātha yathā tathaṃ. "
msgstr "listen to this, for it is the truth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an7.64:18.1"
msgid "Kuddho hi pitaraṃ hanti, "
msgstr "An angry person slays their father; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:18.2"
msgid "hanti kuddho samātaraṃ; "
msgstr "their mother, too, they slay. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:18.3"
msgid "Kuddho hi brāhmaṇaṃ hanti, "
msgstr "An angry person slays a saint; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:18.4"
msgid "hanti kuddho puthujjanaṃ. "
msgstr "a normal person, too, they slay. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an7.64:19.1"
msgid "Yāya mātu bhato poso, "
msgstr "A man is raised by his mother, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:19.2"
msgid "imaṃ lokaṃ avekkhati; "
msgstr "who shows him the world. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:19.3"
msgid "Tampi pāṇadadiṃ santiṃ, "
msgstr "But an angry ordinary person slays "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:19.4"
msgid "hanti kuddho puthujjano. "
msgstr "even that good woman who gave him life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an7.64:20.1"
msgid "Attūpamā hi te sattā, "
msgstr "Like oneself, all sentient beings "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: paramo → paramaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.64:20.2"
msgid "attā hi paramo piyo; "
msgstr "hold themselves most dear. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:20.3"
msgid "Hanti kuddho puthuttānaṃ, "
msgstr "But angry people kill themselves all kinds of ways, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:20.4"
msgid "nānārūpesu mucchito. "
msgstr "distraught for many reasons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "an7.64:21.1"
msgid "Asinā hanti attānaṃ, "
msgstr "Some kill themselves with swords, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:21.2"
msgid "visaṃ khādanti mucchitā; "
msgstr "some, distraught, take poison. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:21.3"
msgid "Rajjuyā bajjha mīyanti, "
msgstr "Some hang themselves with rope, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:21.4"
msgid "pabbatāmapi kandare. "
msgstr "or fling themselves down a mountain gorge. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.98, sc22
#. VAR: Bhūnahaccāni → bhūtahaccāni (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.64:22.1"
msgid "Bhūnahaccāni kammāni, "
msgstr "When they commit deeds of destroying life "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:22.2"
msgid "attamāraṇiyāni ca; "
msgstr "and killing themselves, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Karontā nāvabujjhanti → karonto nāvabujjhati (mr)
msgctxt "an7.64:22.3"
msgid "Karontā nāvabujjhanti, "
msgstr "they don’t realize what they do, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:22.4"
msgid "kodhajāto parābhavo. "
msgstr "for anger leads them to ruin. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "an7.64:23.1"
msgid "Itāyaṃ kodharūpena, "
msgstr "The snare of death in the form of anger "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:23.2"
msgid "maccupāso guhāsayo; "
msgstr "lies hidden in the heart. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:23.3"
msgid "Taṃ damena samucchinde, "
msgstr "You should cut it out by self-control, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:23.4"
msgid "paññāvīriyena diṭṭhiyā. "
msgstr "by wisdom, energy, and right ideas. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
#. VAR: metaṃ → ekametaṃ (bj) | ekamekaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.64:24.1"
msgid "Yathā metaṃ akusalaṃ, "
msgstr "An astute person should cut out "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:24.2"
msgid "samucchindetha paṇḍito; "
msgstr "this unskillful thing. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:24.3"
msgid "Tatheva dhamme sikkhetha, "
msgstr "And they’d train in the teaching in just the same way, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:24.4"
msgid "mā no dummaṅkuyaṃ ahu. "
msgstr "not yielding to sulkiness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "an7.64:25.1"
msgid "Vītakodhā anāyāsā, "
msgstr "Free of anger, free of despair, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: anussukā → anissukā (s1, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.64:25.2"
msgid "Vītalobhā anussukā; "
msgstr "free of greed, with no more longing, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:25.3"
msgid "Dantā kodhaṃ pahantvāna, "
msgstr "tamed, having given up anger, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Parinibbanti anāsavā”ti → parinibbassathanāsavāti (s1-3) | parinibbiṃsu anāsavāti (mr)
msgctxt "an7.64:25.4"
msgid "Parinibbanti anāsavā”ti. "
msgstr "they become extinguished without defilements.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.64:25.5"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.64:25.6"
msgid "Abyākatavaggo chaṭṭho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "an7.64:26.1"
msgid "Abyākato purisagati, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:26.2"
msgid "Tissa sīha arakkhiyaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:26.3"
msgid "Kimilaṃ satta pacalā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.64:26.4"
msgid "Mettā bhariyā kodhekādasāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
